{{Quote|If a squad of seekers locks onto us, these transports aren't equipped with enough firepower to hold them off|[[Githany]]|<ref name="Darth Bane: Path of Destruction">''[[Darth Bane: Path of Destruction]]''</ref>}}
A '''seeker''' was a type of aircraft, a [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] or atmospheric-combat [[Speeder bike/Legends|flyer]], used by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi]] forces of the [[Army of Light/Legends|Army of Light]] during the [[Ruusan campaign]] in the [[New Sith Wars]].

==Characteristics==
They were considered a threat to lightly-armed transports like [[Interloper]]s, but the [[Buzzard (starfighter)|Buzzard]] fighters of the [[Brotherhood of Darkness/Legends|Brotherhood of Darkness]] were thought to be capable of defending against them.

{{Ship-stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The lack of a capital letter perhaps suggests that "seeker" is a generic term rather than a specific designation; but in the same novel, [[corsair battleship]] is left lowercase as well.

